div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- Body -->\r\n  <div class=\"width75 floatRight\">\r\n     <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n         <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script>\r\n<h2>Contact Me</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a></p>    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2012 Stephen Downes ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@mooc.ca\">stephen@mooc.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.mooc.ca\">gRSShopper</a>. \r\nCSS design adapted from <a  href=\"http://fullahead.org\" title=\"Goto Fullahead\">Fullahead</a> </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','no','no','no','1',1292797027,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'contact.htm',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(155,'About OpenID',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1>About OpenID on <st_name></h1>\r\n<h3>What Is OpenID?</h3>\r\n<p>OpenID is a system that allows you to have one identity that you use on any number of websites.</p><p>This way, you don&#39;t have to fill in user information and other details every time you want to create an account (or to simply comment) on a new website (at least - that&#39;s how it will work in the future when the &#39;attribute exchange&#39; protocol is settled).</p><h3>How does it Work?</h3><p>You create an account on an <em><strong>identity provider</strong></em> website. The identity provider website provides you with a URL. This URL is your OpenID identity.</p><p>Then, when you want to login to a new website, look for the small OpenID logo <img src=\"http://connect.mooc.ca/images/openid-inputicon.gif\" alt=\"\" data-mce-src=\"http://connect.mooc.ca/images/openid-inputicon.gif\"> in the login form. Type your OpenID into the form and click the Login button.</p><p>When you click the login button, the new website sends you back to the URL you provided as your OpenID identity. That&#39;s where you login, at your OpenID provider. If you successfully login, then you are returned to the new site.</p><p>What&#39;s the point of this? The idea here is that you prove that <em>you</em> are the person who is able tolog into your site. If you keep your password secret, nobody else can prove that they&#39;re you - and you can prove to anyone else that you are!</p><h3>Where Do I get an OpenID URL?</h3><p>From an identity provider.</p><p>Stephen&#39;s Web is not yet an identity provider (that&#39;s phase 2) - and even when it is, you may want a site that&#39;s a bit more reliable.</p><p>Here is a list of OpenID providers (I selected LiveJournal).</p><ul><li><a href=\"http://openid.org/\" data-mce-href=\"http://openid.org/\">OpenID.org</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myopenid.com/\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.myopenid.com/\">MyOpenID</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li><li><a href=\"https://www.livejournal.com\" data-mce-href=\"https://www.livejournal.com\">LiveJournal</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li><li><a href=\"http://www.aol.com/\" data-mce-href=\"http://www.aol.com/\">AOL</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li></ul><h3>Websites</h3><ul><li><a href=\"http://openid.net/\" data-mce-href=\"http://openid.net/\">OpenID</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li><li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenID\" data-mce-href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenID\">Wikipedia page on OpenID</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li><li><a href=\"http://janrain.com/openid\" data-mce-href=\"http://janrain.com/openid\">JanRain OpenID</a><br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></li></ul><h3>Whatever happened to...?</h3><p>You&#39;re probably thinking of <a href=\"http://mooc.ca/midm.htm\" data-mce-href=\"http://mooc.ca/midm.htm\">mIDm</a>, a distributed login system I developed a little while ago.</p><p>It was based on the ideas in my paper <a href=\"http://mooc.ca/post/12\" data-mce-href=\"http://mooc.ca/post/12\">Authentication and Identification</a>. The idea was that a system that let people self-identify was good enough for the web; that all these systems that demanded some sort of authentication were asking too much.</p><p>After all, the person who should benefit from a login system is <em>you</em>, not the people who are requiring the login.</p><p>Anyhow, a few days after I launched mIDm, Brad Fitzpatrick of LiveJournal launched OpenID based on the same principles and using almost exactly the same mechanism (the really big difference was that I wanted people to put their URL in their browser header).</p><p>OpenID is the system that caught on. Which is perfectly fine with me - I&#39;ve always seen OpenID as a validation of what I was saying at the time (and am still saying today), and I like to think of mIDm as a validation of what Brad Fitzpatrick was - and is - still saying.</p><p>And nobody <em>owns</em> OpenID, nobody&#39;s demanding licensing, and nobody&#39;s forcing you though a single point of login failure, which is exactly the way it should be.</p><h3>The OpenID Login Form</h3><form action=\"&lt;st_url&gt;cgi-bin/login.cgi\" method=\"post\"><input name=\"action\" value=\"OpenID\" type=\"hidden\"> <input name=\"refer\" value=\"\" type=\"hidden\"> <strong>Your OpenID URL:</strong> <input id=\"openid_url\" class=\"sexy\" name=\"openid_url\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\"> <input style=\"background: #ff6200; color: #fff;\" value=\"Login\" data-mce-style=\"background: #ff6200; color: #fff;\" type=\"submit\"><br>For example: <tt>melody.someblog.com</tt> (if your host supports OpenID)</form><p>&nbsp;</p>','Friday','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"\r\n    \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\r\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xml:lang=\"en\" lang=\"en-AU\">\r\n\r\n<!-- mooc.ca template page_header -->\r\n\r\n<head>\r\n\r\n<!-- title -->\r\n  <title>About OpenID ~ Connectivism &amp; Connective Knowledge 2012</title>\r\n\r\n<!-- scripts -->\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/downes.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.jdpicker.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- style -->\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/jdpicker.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/html.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/layout.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv\" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/print.css\" media=\"print\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- links -->  \r\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/favicon.ico\" type=\"image/x-icon\"/>\r\n  <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" title=\"RSS\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.xml\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"application/xhtml+xml; charset=utf-8\" />\r\n\r\n<!-- meta -->\r\n  <meta name=\"author\" content=\"mooc.ca\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"Connectivism and Connective Knowledge,Massive Open Online Course,MOOC,online learning,new media,e-learning,RSS,syndication,connectivism,learning,education\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"cck11.MOOC.ca\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- CONTENT div: Holds all site content except for the footer.  This is what causes the footer to stick to the bottom -->\r\n<div id=\"content\">\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- HEADER: Holds title, subtitle and header images -->\r\n  <div id=\"header\">\r\n\r\n      <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/\"><img src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/images/moocheader.gif\" alt=\"mooc.ca\" border=\"0\"/></a>\r\n      <hr>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- MAIN MENU: Top horizontal menu of the site.  Use class=\"here\" to turn the current page tab on -->\r\n  <div id=\"mainMenu\">\r\n    <ul class=\"floatRight\">\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\" title=\"Introduction\">Home</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\" title=\"About\">About</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\" title=\"Get in touch\" class=\"last\">Contact</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- PAGE CONTENT BEGINS: This is where you would define the columns (number, width and alignment) -->\r\n  <div id=\"page\">\r\n\r\n    <!-- Sidebar -->\r\n   <div class=\"width25 floatLeft leftColumn\">\r\n      <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n           <h2 style=\"margin-left:10px;\">Contents</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:10px;\">\r\n\r\n<b>This Course</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\">Home Page</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\">About This Course</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/outline.htm\">Course Outline</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/how.htm\">How It Works</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/facilitators.htm\">Course Facilitators</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/privacy.htm\">Your Privacy</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\">Contact Us</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Your Account</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi?action=Register\">Register</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi\">Login</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/options.htm\">Manage Account</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/openid.htm\">About OpenID</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Participating</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/cchat.cgi\">Join a Backchannel Chat</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/threads.htm\">Read Discussion Threads</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.htm\">Read Daily Newsletter</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/archives.htm\">Newsletter Archives</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?action=viewer\">Browse Blog Posts</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/new_feed.htm\">Add a New Blog Feed</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feeds.htm\">View List of Blogs</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/recordings.htm\">Listen to Recordings</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Feeds</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyposts.xml\">Announcements RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyblogs.xml\">Blog Posts RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/opml.xml\">OPML List of Feeds</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Contents</b><br />\r\nTBA - will be posted before January 23 - see <a  href=\"http://cck11.mooc.ca\">CCK11 contents</a> for a good indication of what we\'ll do.\r\n</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- Body -->\r\n  <div class=\"width75 floatRight\">\r\n     <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n         <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script>\r\n<h1>About OpenID on Connectivism &amp; Connective Knowledge 2012</h1>\r\n\r\n<h3>What Is OpenID?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>OpenID is a system that allows you to have one identity that you use on any number of websites.</p>\r\n<p>This way, you don\'t have to fill in user information and other details every time you want to create an account (or to simply comment) on a new website (at least - that\'s how it will work in the future when the \'attribute exchange\' protocol is settled).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How does it Work?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You create an account on an <i><b>identity provider</b></i> website. The identity provider website provides you with a URL. This URL is your OpenID identity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then, when you want to login to a new website, look for the small OpenID logo <img src=\"http://connect.mooc.ca/images/openid-inputicon.gif\"/> in the login form. Type your OpenID into the form and click the Login button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you click the login button, the new website sends you back to the URL you provided as your OpenID identity. That\'s where you login, at your OpenID provider. If you successfully login, then you are returned to the new site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What\'s the point of this? The idea here is that you prove that <i>you</i> are the person who is able to </i>log into your site</i>. If you keep your password secret, nobody else can prove that they\'re you - and you can prove to anyone else that you are!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Where Do I get an OpenID URL?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>From an identity provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stephen\'s Web is not yet an identity provider (that\'s phase 2) - and even when it is, you may want a site that\'s a bit more reliable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is a list of OpenID providers (I selected LiveJournal).</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a  href=\"http://openid.org/\">OpenID.org</a></li>\r\n<li><a  href=\"https://www.myopenid.com/\">MyOpenID</a></li>\r\n\r\n<li><a  href=\"https://www.livejournal.com\">LiveJournal</a></li>\r\n<li><a  href=\"http://www.aol.com/\">AOL</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Websites</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a  href=\"http://openid.net/\">OpenID</a></li>\r\n<li><a  href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenID\">Wikipedia page on OpenID</a></li>\r\n<li><a  href=\"http://janrain.com/openid\">JanRain OpenID</a></li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Whatever happened to...?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You\'re probably thinking of <a  href=\"http://mooc.ca/midm.htm\">mIDm</a>, a distributed login system I developed a little while ago.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was based on the ideas in my paper <a  href=\"http://mooc.ca/post/12\">Authentication and Identification</a>. The idea was that a system that let people self-identify was good enough for the web; that all these systems that demanded some sort of authentication were asking too much.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After all, the person who should benefit from a login system is <i>you</i>, not the people who are requiring the login. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anyhow, a few days after I launched mIDm, Brad Fitzpatrick of LiveJournal launched OpenID based on the same principles and using almost exactly the same mechanism (the really big difference was that I wanted people to put their URL in their browser header).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>OpenID is the system that caught on. Which is perfectly fine with me - I\'ve always seen OpenID as a validation of what I was saying at the time (and am still saying today), and I like to think of mIDm as a validation of what Brad Fitzpatrick was - and is - still saying.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And nobody <i>owns</i> OpenID, nobody\'s demanding licensing, and nobody\'s forcing you though a single point of login failure, which is exactly the way it should be.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The OpenID Login Form</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n		<form method=\"post\" action=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi\">\r\n\r\n		<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"action\" value=\"OpenID\">\r\n		<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"refer\" value=\"\">\r\n		<nobr><b>Your OpenID URL:</b> <input class=\"sexy\" id=\"openid_url\" name=\"openid_url\" size=\"30\" />\r\n<input style=\"background: #ff6200; color: #fff;\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Login\" /></nobr><br />For example: <tt>melody.someblog.com</tt> (if your host supports OpenID)</form>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@mooc.ca\">stephen@mooc.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.mooc.ca\">gRSShopper</a>. \r\nCSS design adapted from <a  href=\"http://fullahead.org\" title=\"Goto Fullahead\">Fullahead</a> </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','no','no','no','1',1292805319,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'openid.htm',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,'Add a New Feed',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1>Add A New Feed</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><br/><b>Share Your RSS Feed</b><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nWe would like you to share blog posts and other online content with us. Here&#39;s how the process works:<br/>\r\n- you create a blog or some other content somewhere on the internet<br/>\r\n- you find the RSS feed of that content and share it with is <a href=\"<st_url>new_feed.htm\">here, on the &#39;New Feed&#39; page</a><br/>\r\n- we look at your feed, to make sure all the links work properly, and then place it on the <a href=\"<st_url>feeds.htm\">course feeds</a> page (note that it might take a day or two to approve new feeds)<br/>\r\n- you write a blog post or other content using the tag <st_tag> (that is, you put the tag &#39;<st_tag>&#39; somewhere in the title or text of your post, or as a category for your post<br/>\r\n- we retrieve your post and display it here in the newsletter and elsewhere in the course (more on that to come)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need more detailed instructions, you can view one of the videos we&#39;ve produced describing the process for other courses:<br/>\r\n- <a href=\"http://downes.blip.tv/file/4105170/\">Here it is for the PLENK course</a><br/>\r\n- <a href=\"http://downes.blip.tv/file/3729449/\">Here it is for the Critical Literacies course</a><br/>\r\nThe only difference between this course and the other courses is in (a) where to add a new feed, and (b) the course tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New feeds: <a href=\"<st_url>new_feed.htm\"><st_url>new_feed.htm</a><br/>\r\nCourse Tag: <st_tag></p>\r\n<p><br/><b>Fill out the form below to share your feed:<br/></p>\r\n<p>\r\n 		 <form method=\"post\" action=\"<st_url>cgi-bin/page.cgi\">\r\n		 <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"table\" value=\"feed\">\r\n		 <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"id\" value=\"new\">\r\n		 <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"action\" value=\"update\">\r\n		 <table border=1 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 style=\"color:#91c6e7\">\r\n\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>Title</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_title\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>Author</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_authorname\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>RSS File URL</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_link\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n\r\n		\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>Web Page URL</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_html\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"feed_type\" value=\"RSS 2.0\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		\r\n		<tr><td colspan=\"4\">Description<br/>\r\n		<textarea name=\"feed_description\" cols=\"60\" rows=\"15\"></textarea></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		\r\n<tr><td colspan=\"4\"><input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\"></td></tr></table></form>\r\n\r\n</p>','Friday','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"\r\n    \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\r\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xml:lang=\"en\" lang=\"en-AU\">\r\n\r\n<!-- mooc.ca template page_header -->\r\n\r\n<head>\r\n\r\n<!-- title -->\r\n  <title>Add a New Feed ~ CCK11</title>\r\n\r\n<!-- scripts -->\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/downes.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.jdpicker.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- style -->\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/jdpicker.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/html.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/layout.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv\" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/print.css\" media=\"print\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- links -->  \r\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/favicon.ico\" type=\"image/x-icon\"/>\r\n  <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" title=\"RSS\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.xml\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"application/xhtml+xml; charset=utf-8\" />\r\n\r\n<!-- meta -->\r\n  <meta name=\"author\" content=\"mooc.ca\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"Connectivism and Connective Knowledge,Massive Open Online Course,MOOC,online learning,new media,e-learning,RSS,syndication,connectivism,learning,education\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"cck11.MOOC.ca\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- CONTENT div: Holds all site content except for the footer.  This is what causes the footer to stick to the bottom -->\r\n<div id=\"content\">\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- HEADER: Holds title, subtitle and header images -->\r\n  <div id=\"header\">\r\n\r\n      <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/\"><img src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/images/moocheader.jpg\" alt=\"mooc.ca\" border=\"0\"/></a>\r\n      <hr>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- MAIN MENU: Top horizontal menu of the site.  Use class=\"here\" to turn the current page tab on -->\r\n  <div id=\"mainMenu\">\r\n    <ul class=\"floatRight\">\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\" title=\"Introduction\">Home</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\" title=\"About\">About</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\" title=\"Get in touch\" class=\"last\">Contact</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- PAGE CONTENT BEGINS: This is where you would define the columns (number, width and alignment) -->\r\n  <div id=\"page\">\r\n\r\n    <!-- Sidebar -->\r\n   <div class=\"width25 floatLeft leftColumn\">\r\n      <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n           <h2 style=\"margin-left:10px;\">Contents</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:10px;\">\r\n\r\n<b>This Course</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\">Home Page</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\">About This Course</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/outline.htm\">Course Outline</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/how.htm\">How It Works</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/facilitators.htm\">Course Facilitators</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/privacy.htm\">Your Privacy</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\">Contact Us</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Your Account</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi?action=Register\">Register</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi\">Login</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/options.htm\">Manage Account</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/openid.htm\">About OpenID</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Participating</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/cchat.cgi\">Join a Backchannel Chat</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/threads.htm\">Read Discussion Threads</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.htm\">Read Daily Newsletter</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/archives.htm\">Newsletter Archives</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?action=viewer\">Browse Blog Posts</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/new_feed.htm\">Add a New Blog Feed</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feeds.htm\">View List of Blogs</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/recordings.htm\">Listen to Recordings</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Feeds</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyposts.xml\">Announcements RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyblogs.xml\">Blog Posts RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/opml.xml\">OPML List of Feeds</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Contents</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week1.htm\">Week 1</a>: Connectivism? <br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week2.htm\">Week 2</a>: Patterns<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week3.htm\">Week 3</a>: Knowledge<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week4.htm\">Week 4</a>: Unique?<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week5.htm\">Week 5</a>: Groups, Networks<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week6.htm\">Week 6</a>: PLENK<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week7.htm\">Week 7</a>: Adaptive Systems<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week8.htm\">Week 8</a>: Power & Authority <br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week9.htm\">Week 9</a>: Openness<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week10.htm\">Week 10</a>: Net Pedagogy<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week11.htm\">Week 11</a>: Research & Analytics<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week12.htm\">Week 12</a>: Changing views<br /><br />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- Body -->\r\n  <div class=\"width75 floatRight\">\r\n     <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n         <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script>\r\n<h1>Add A New Feed</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Share Your RSS Feed</b>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe would like you to share blog posts and other online content with us. Here&#39;s how the process works:\r\n\r\n- you create a blog or some other content somewhere on the internet\r\n\r\n- you find the RSS feed of that content and share it with is <a  href=\"http://mooc.ca/new_feed.htm\">here, on the &#39;New Feed&#39; page</a>\r\n\r\n- we look at your feed, to make sure all the links work properly, and then place it on the <a  href=\"http://mooc.ca/feeds.htm\">course feeds</a> page (note that it might take a day or two to approve new feeds)\r\n\r\n- you write a blog post or other content using the tag CCK11 (that is, you put the tag &#39;CCK11&#39; somewhere in the title or text of your post, or as a category for your post\r\n\r\n- we retrieve your post and display it here in the newsletter and elsewhere in the course (more on that to come)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need more detailed instructions, you can view one of the videos we&#39;ve produced describing the process for other courses:\r\n\r\n- <a  href=\"http://downes.blip.tv/file/4105170/\">Here it is for the PLENK course</a>\r\n\r\n- <a  href=\"http://downes.blip.tv/file/3729449/\">Here it is for the Critical Literacies course</a>\r\n\r\nThe only difference between this course and the other courses is in (a) where to add a new feed, and (b) the course tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New feeds: <a  href=\"http://mooc.ca/new_feed.htm\">http://mooc.ca/new_feed.htm</a>\r\n\r\nCourse Tag: CCK11</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Fill out the form below to share your feed:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n 		 <form method=\"post\" action=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi\">\r\n		 <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"table\" value=\"feed\">\r\n		 <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"id\" value=\"new\">\r\n		 <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"action\" value=\"update\">\r\n		 <table border=1 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 style=\"color:#91c6e7\">\r\n\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>Title</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_title\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>Author</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_authorname\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>RSS File URL</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_link\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n\r\n		\r\n		<tr>\r\n		<td>Web Page URL</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<input type=\"text\" name=\"feed_html\" value=\"\" size=\"40\">\r\n		<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"feed_type\" value=\"RSS 2.0\" size=\"40\">\r\n		</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		\r\n		<tr><td colspan=\"4\">Description\r\n\r\n		<textarea name=\"feed_description\" cols=\"60\" rows=\"15\"></textarea></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		\r\n<tr><td colspan=\"4\"><input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\"></td></tr></table></form>\r\n\r\n</p>    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@mooc.ca\">stephen@mooc.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.mooc.ca\">gRSShopper</a>. \r\nCSS design adapted from <a  href=\"http://fullahead.org\" title=\"Goto Fullahead\">Fullahead</a> </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','no','no','no','1',1292805581,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'new_feed.htm',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(157,'Archives',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<html>\r\n<head>\r\n<META HTTP-EQUIV=\"refresh\" \r\nCONTENT=\"1;URL=<st_url>cgi-bin/archive.cgi?page=newsletter.htm\">\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\nLoading archives....\r\n</body>\r\n</html>','Friday','<html>\r\n<head>\r\n<META HTTP-EQUIV=\"refresh\" \r\nCONTENT=\"1;URL=http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/archive.cgi?page=newsletter.htm\">\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\nLoading archives....\r\n</body>\r\n</html>',NULL,'HTML',NULL,NULL,'no','no','no','1',1292805752,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'archives.htm',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(159,'Create a Backchannel',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h2>Create Your Own Backchannel</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A backchannel is a live text chat created for a specific presentation or event. You can create your own custom backchannel using this form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can edit this form later (just <a href=\"<st_url>cgi-bin/cchat.cgi\">go here</a>), but you need to enter the values here to get your backchannel started:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><form method=\"post\" action=\"<st_url>cgi-bin/page.cgi\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"db\" value=\"thread\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"id\" value=\"new\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"action\" value=\"update\">\r\n\r\n<table style=\"margin-left:20px;\">\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Topic</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\"><input type=\"text\" size=\"50\" name=\"thread_title\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\">Description<br/>\r\n<textarea name=\"thread_description\" rows=\"4\" cols=\"60\"></textarea></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\"><input type=\"submit\" size=\"60\" value=\"Create Thread\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n</form>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Happy Backchanneling!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to create a backchannel, you much be a registered user on this site and logged in. If you are not logged in, <a href=\"<st_url>cgi-bin/login.cgi?refer=<st_url>create_backchannel.htm\">go login now</a>. After logging in, select &#39;return to where you were&#39; to come back to this page.</p>\r\n','Friday','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"\r\n    \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\r\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xml:lang=\"en\" lang=\"en-AU\">\r\n\r\n<!-- mooc.ca template page_header -->\r\n\r\n<head>\r\n\r\n<!-- title -->\r\n  <title>Create a Backchannel ~ CCK11</title>\r\n\r\n<!-- scripts -->\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/downes.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.jdpicker.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- style -->\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/jdpicker.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/html.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/layout.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv\" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/print.css\" media=\"print\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- links -->  \r\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/favicon.ico\" type=\"image/x-icon\"/>\r\n  <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" title=\"RSS\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.xml\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"application/xhtml+xml; charset=utf-8\" />\r\n\r\n<!-- meta -->\r\n  <meta name=\"author\" content=\"mooc.ca\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"Connectivism and Connective Knowledge,Massive Open Online Course,MOOC,online learning,new media,e-learning,RSS,syndication,connectivism,learning,education\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"cck11.MOOC.ca\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- CONTENT div: Holds all site content except for the footer.  This is what causes the footer to stick to the bottom -->\r\n<div id=\"content\">\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- HEADER: Holds title, subtitle and header images -->\r\n  <div id=\"header\">\r\n\r\n      <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/\"><img src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/images/moocheader.jpg\" alt=\"mooc.ca\" border=\"0\"/></a>\r\n      <hr>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- MAIN MENU: Top horizontal menu of the site.  Use class=\"here\" to turn the current page tab on -->\r\n  <div id=\"mainMenu\">\r\n    <ul class=\"floatRight\">\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\" title=\"Introduction\">Home</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\" title=\"About\">About</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\" title=\"Get in touch\" class=\"last\">Contact</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- PAGE CONTENT BEGINS: This is where you would define the columns (number, width and alignment) -->\r\n  <div id=\"page\">\r\n\r\n    <!-- Sidebar -->\r\n   <div class=\"width25 floatLeft leftColumn\">\r\n      <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n           <h2 style=\"margin-left:10px;\">Contents</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:10px;\">\r\n\r\n<b>This Course</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\">Home Page</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\">About This Course</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/outline.htm\">Course Outline</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/how.htm\">How It Works</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/facilitators.htm\">Course Facilitators</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/privacy.htm\">Your Privacy</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\">Contact Us</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Your Account</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi?action=Register\">Register</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi\">Login</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/options.htm\">Manage Account</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/openid.htm\">About OpenID</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Participating</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/cchat.cgi\">Join a Backchannel Chat</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/threads.htm\">Read Discussion Threads</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.htm\">Read Daily Newsletter</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/archives.htm\">Newsletter Archives</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?action=viewer\">Browse Blog Posts</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/new_feed.htm\">Add a New Blog Feed</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feeds.htm\">View List of Blogs</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/recordings.htm\">Listen to Recordings</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Feeds</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyposts.xml\">Announcements RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyblogs.xml\">Blog Posts RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/opml.xml\">OPML List of Feeds</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Contents</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week1.htm\">Week 1</a>: Connectivism? <br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week2.htm\">Week 2</a>: Patterns<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week3.htm\">Week 3</a>: Knowledge<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week4.htm\">Week 4</a>: Unique?<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week5.htm\">Week 5</a>: Groups, Networks<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week6.htm\">Week 6</a>: PLENK<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week7.htm\">Week 7</a>: Adaptive Systems<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week8.htm\">Week 8</a>: Power &amp; Authority <br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week9.htm\">Week 9</a>: Openness<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week10.htm\">Week 10</a>: Net Pedagogy<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week11.htm\">Week 11</a>: Research &amp; Analytics<br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/week12.htm\">Week 12</a>: Changing views<br /><br />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- Body -->\r\n  <div class=\"width75 floatRight\">\r\n     <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n         <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script>\r\n<h2>Create Your Own Backchannel</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A backchannel is a live text chat created for a specific presentation or event. You can create your own custom backchannel using this form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can edit this form later (just <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/cchat.cgi\">go here</a>), but you need to enter the values here to get your backchannel started:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><form method=\"post\" action=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"db\" value=\"thread\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"id\" value=\"new\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"action\" value=\"update\">\r\n\r\n<table style=\"margin-left:20px;\">\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Topic</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\"><input type=\"text\" size=\"50\" name=\"thread_title\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\">Description<br/>\r\n<textarea name=\"thread_description\" rows=\"4\" cols=\"60\"></textarea></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\"><input type=\"submit\" size=\"60\" value=\"Create Thread\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n</form>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Happy Backchanneling!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to create a backchannel, you much be a registered user on this site and logged in. If you are not logged in, <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi?refer=http://cck12.mooc.ca/create_backchannel.htm\">go login now</a>. After logging in, select \'return to where you were\' to come back to this page.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@mooc.ca\">stephen@mooc.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.mooc.ca\">gRSShopper</a>. \r\nCSS design adapted from <a  href=\"http://fullahead.org\" title=\"Goto Fullahead\">Fullahead</a> </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','no','no','no','1',1293387267,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'create_backchannel.htm',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,'NRC01PL Daily Newsletter',NULL,NULL,'htm','<h2>Discussion Posts</h2>\r\n<p style=\"font: 400 12pt/16pt Verdana,Arial, sans-serif; color: #000040;\">Discussion posts will be available here.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Delicious Links</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font: 400 12pt/16pt Verdana,Arial, sans-serif; color: #000040;\">Links from the shared bookmarking site delicious. <a href=\"http://www.delicious.com/tag/cck11\">Add your own bookmarks</a> and be sure to tag them as CCK11.</p>\r\n\r\n<keyword db=link;expires=24;truncate=500;format=email;all;sort=crdate DESC>\r\n\r\n<keyword db=link;expires=24;truncate=500;format=email;all;sort=crdate DESC>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Twitter Posts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font: 400 10pt/12pt Verdana,Arial, sans-serif;color:#000040;\">\r\n<keyword db=link;type=twitter;format=twitter;sort=crdate DESC;expires=72>\r\n</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,'<p>Welcome to #NRC01PL. This is your daily newsletter!<p>\r\n\r\n#TODAY#\r\n\r\n<keyword db=post;type=announcement;format=announcement_html;heading=Announcements;sort=crdate;expires=15;all>\r\n\r\n<keyword db=post;type=link;format=link_email;sort=crdate DESC;expires=20;number=4;heading=Resources;all>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"width:450px;\">\r\n<keyword db=link;format=twitter;sort=crdate;expires=72;number=100;heading=Twitter Posts;all>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, to make it easy for us to find your contributions, any time you write about the course, use the course hashtag: <b>#NRC01PL</b></p>\r\n\r\n','Monday,Tuesday,Wednesday,Thursday,Friday','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n<title>NRC01PL Daily Newsletter ~ by Stephen Downes</title>\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\r\n<STYLE TYPE=\"text/css\">\r\n  a {color:#44708B; }\r\n</STYLE>\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n<body style=\"background: #ffffff;\">\r\n<p><a  href=\"https://openedx.lpss.me/\"><img src=\"http://course.downes.ca/images/Newsletter_Banner.jpg\" width=100% border=0></a></p>\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav Bar -->\r\n<p \"style=\"font: 400 1.6em verdana, arial, sans-serif;\">\r\n[<a  href=\"https://openedx.lpss.me/\">Course Page</a>]\r\n[<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/cgi-bin/archive.cgi?page=newsletter.htm\">Newsletter Archives</a>]</p>\r\n\r\n	<div style=\"border-top: 1px solid #6cbcee;font: 400 1.0em verdana, arial, sans-serif;;margin-top:30px;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Welcome to #NRC01PL. This is your daily newsletter!<p>\r\n\r\nApr 07, 2016\r\n\r\n<h2>Announcements</h2><!-- Begin Post -->\r\n<h3>Arke</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.downes.ca/files/arkeJPG.JPG\" width=\"500\"><br /><br />\r\nThe last week of the Personal Learning MOOC was intended to showcase Arke, the next generation version of LPSS that has been under development for several months now.<br /><br />\r\nHowever, NRC has changed the leadership of the LPSS program, and the new leadership has discontinued work on personal learning. NRC will now focus on learning analytics and automated learning paths.<br /><br />\r\nFor these reasons, we were left without any content to deliver for the last week of the course. There are additionally now no means to deliver recognition or certification, however, for those who ask (and who participated in the course) I will offer a personal certificate.<br /><br />\r\nThank you for your participation in the course. Please be sure to complete the final course survey, as this supports the ongoing research of the National Research Council.<p></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Resources</h2><!-- Begin Post -->\r\n<div><strong><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/post/8832/rd\">Final Course Survey</a></strong><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n 2016/04/07<hr size=\"1\" color=\"#cccccc\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\"/>\r\n<p>We invite you to participate in our Personal Learning MOOC end of course survey. The survey is anonymous and voluntary. Please click on the link below if you are interested in knowing more about the survey and how to participate. Thank you!\r\n<a  href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/NRC01PL_final\">https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/NRC01PL_final</a>\r\n [<a  href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/NRC01PL_final\">Direct Link</a>] \r\n</div><div><hr size=\"1\"></div>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n<div><strong><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/post/8831/rd\">Personal Learning MOOC mid-course survey results</a></strong><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n 2016/04/07<hr size=\"1\" color=\"#cccccc\" style=\"margin:0px;padding:0px;\"/>\r\n<p>As promised, here are the Personal Learning Course midcourse survey results. Click on the links (ie., the title of this post) to download the PowerPoint slides. A <a  href=\"Personal Learning MOOC mid-course survey results.pdf\">PDF version</a> is also available. [<a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/files/Personal Learning MOOC mid-course survey results.pptx\">Direct Link</a>] \r\n</div><div><hr size=\"1\"></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"width:450px;\">\r\n<h2>Twitter Posts</h2><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/JRDingwall/status/717040804632498176\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/638215996944224256/351RjP6J_normal.jpg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/JRDingwall/status/717040804632498176\">@JRDingwall</a>: Just bumped into  <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23nrc01pl&src=hash\">#nrc01pl</a> is there a course hub at all or entirely a network of participants\' blogs? (Mon Apr 04 17:27:04)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717056098742747137\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717056098742747137\">@fgraver</a>: <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/JRDingwall\">@JRDingwall</a> Theres a very quiet course hub on OpenEdX, but theres also a (slightly less quiet) Google+ community. #NRC01PL (Mon Apr 04 18:27:50)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"http://teachonline.ca/tools-trends/exploring-future-education/2016-look-future-online-learning-part-1\">@</a> tweeted: <br>								Tags:				        	        Onlineteaching	      			 Thu, 11 Feb 2016 16:46:44 +0000<br/><br/><a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/presentation/376\">@</a> tweeted: <br>								Tags:				        	        via:packrati.us	      			 Sun, 06 Mar 2016 00:45:25 +0000<br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717378931016466433\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717378931016466433\">@fgraver</a>: <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a>  https://t.co/UckgfGHcx6 (Tue Apr 05 15:50:40)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717378854722080768\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717378854722080768\">@fgraver</a>: <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> Thats a surprise. https://t.co/Z5PKO2vurs (Tue Apr 05 15:50:21)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/koutropoulos/status/717382653012549632\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1476171910/2_normal.png\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/koutropoulos/status/717382653012549632\">@koutropoulos</a>: Hey! <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/gsiemens\">@gsiemens</a> is on last Fridays <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> hangout. always fun to listen to george :) https://t.co/ceZ5KX0en6 (Tue Apr 05 16:05:27)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717410062139068417\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717410062139068417\">@fgraver</a>: Wasnt there a hangout planned for <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> today? Cant find it anywhere. Any connection to <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/Downes\">@Downes</a> change of responsibilities? (Tue Apr 05 17:54:22)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717649698484568064\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717649698484568064\">@fgraver</a>: Anyone heard word from <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/Downes\">@Downes</a> on whats happening in <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL?&src=hash\">#NRC01PL?</a> Would love to complete the MOOC, but perhaps its been shelved? (Wed Apr 06 09:46:36)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/koutropoulos/status/717699998847221760\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1476171910/2_normal.png\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/koutropoulos/status/717699998847221760\">@koutropoulos</a>: cranky pants reviewer tackles  are MOOCs the answer?  https://t.co/DiZ9dJUXSE - maybe of interest to #NRC01PL (Wed Apr 06 13:06:28)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717720709687078912\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717720709687078912\">@fgraver</a>: It\'s week 7, and there should be <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> readings... Here\'s my entry for a Wednesday. https://t.co/M79pD4yE2K (Wed Apr 06 14:28:46)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/onewheeljoe/status/717746199789318144\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/688124902050664448/1YRmR_BM_normal.jpg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/onewheeljoe/status/717746199789318144\">@onewheeljoe</a>: Looking into the different platforms for <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL.&src=hash\">#NRC01PL.</a> What is Arke? I\'ve seen it mentioned but can\'t find a defn/explanation. (Wed Apr 06 16:10:03)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717772579822501888\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717772579822501888\">@fgraver</a>: <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/onewheeljoe\">@onewheeljoe</a> We were supposed to get to see it this week. But seems like with the change in <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/Downes\">@Downes</a> employment status thats gone. (Wed Apr 06 17:54:53)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717776303718535169\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/524483560137166848/45taFCxw_normal.jpeg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/fgraver/status/717776303718535169\">@fgraver</a>: Another <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> week 7 reading. https://t.co/PJwYEgVIwM (Wed Apr 06 18:09:41)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/maksmom13/status/718037134049849345\">@</a> tweeted: <div class=\"tweet\" style=\"clear:both;\"> \n					<img src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/461053458/merle_small_normal.jpg\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\">\n					<a  href=\"https://twitter.com/maksmom13/status/718037134049849345\">@maksmom13</a>: elearnspace  learning, networks, blog by GSiemens guest on Friday hangout <a  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23NRC01PL&src=hash\">#NRC01PL</a> https://t.co/PVdxXmymZs via @Diigo (Thu Apr 07 11:26:07)</div> <br/><br/><a  href=\"http://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/en//pubs/archive/35179.pdf\">@</a> tweeted: <br>								Tags:				        	        machine learning	      			 Tue, 16 Feb 2016 23:28:38 +0000<br/><br/>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, to make it easy for us to find your contributions, any time you write about the course, use the course hashtag: <b>#NRC01PL</b></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n	<div style=\"border-top: 1px solid #6cbcee;font: small-caps 100 8pt arial,sans-serif;margin-top:30px;\">\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"float:right;\">Copyright 2016 Stephen Downes - National Research Council Canada\r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n		<p>\r\nThis newsletter is sent only at the request of subscribers. If you would like to unsubscribe,\r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi?action=Unsub&pid=PERSON&sid=SUBSCRIBER\" style=\"color: #0fad0f; text-decoration: none;\">Click here</a>.<br /><br />\r\nThis work is licensed under a\r\n\r\n		<a  href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\">Creative Commons License</a>.\r\n		</p>\r\n		\r\n	</div>\r\n			\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n',NULL,'email','email_header','email_footer','no','no','no','1',1293639484,1460004602,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'newsletter.htm','1460051149','no','Daily','17',NULL,'00','no','Monday,Tuesday,Wednesday,Thursday,Friday'),(163,'Feeds',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<br>\r\n<h1><st_name> Participant Feeds</h1>\r\n<p>The following is a list of the feeds harvested as part of the <st_name> course. This list may also be obtained as an <a href=\"<st_url>opml.xml\">OPML File</a>. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<keyword db=feed;format=course;number=300;sort=title;status=A;all>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nDon&#39;t see your feed? <a href=\"<st_url>options.htm\">Login</a> (if you are not currently logged in), then add it <a href=\"<st_url>new_feed.htm\">using this form</a>. Please note that new feeds wait for approval before they are added to the list (it&#39;s the only way to avoid spam feeds).\r\n</p>','Friday','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"\r\n    \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\r\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xml:lang=\"en\" lang=\"en-AU\">\r\n\r\n<!-- mooc.ca template page_header -->\r\n\r\n<head>\r\n\r\n<!-- title -->\r\n  <title>Feeds ~ Connectivism &amp; Connective Knowledge 2012</title>\r\n\r\n<!-- scripts -->\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/downes.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.js\"></script>\r\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/js/jquery.jdpicker.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- style -->\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/jdpicker.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/html.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv \" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/layout.css\" media=\"screen, projection, tv\" />\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/css/print.css\" media=\"print\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- links -->  \r\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/favicon.ico\" type=\"image/x-icon\"/>\r\n  <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" title=\"RSS\" href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.xml\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"application/xhtml+xml; charset=utf-8\" />\r\n\r\n<!-- meta -->\r\n  <meta name=\"author\" content=\"mooc.ca\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"Connectivism and Connective Knowledge,Massive Open Online Course,MOOC,online learning,new media,e-learning,RSS,syndication,connectivism,learning,education\" />\r\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"cck11.MOOC.ca\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- CONTENT div: Holds all site content except for the footer.  This is what causes the footer to stick to the bottom -->\r\n<div id=\"content\">\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- HEADER: Holds title, subtitle and header images -->\r\n  <div id=\"header\">\r\n\r\n      <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/\"><img src=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/images/moocheader.gif\" alt=\"mooc.ca\" border=\"0\"/></a>\r\n      <hr>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- MAIN MENU: Top horizontal menu of the site.  Use class=\"here\" to turn the current page tab on -->\r\n  <div id=\"mainMenu\">\r\n    <ul class=\"floatRight\">\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\" title=\"Introduction\">Home</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\" title=\"About\">About</a></li>\r\n      <li><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\" title=\"Get in touch\" class=\"last\">Contact</a></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- PAGE CONTENT BEGINS: This is where you would define the columns (number, width and alignment) -->\r\n  <div id=\"page\">\r\n\r\n    <!-- Sidebar -->\r\n   <div class=\"width25 floatLeft leftColumn\">\r\n      <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n           <h2 style=\"margin-left:10px;\">Contents</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:10px;\">\r\n\r\n<b>This Course</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/index.html\">Home Page</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/about.htm\">About This Course</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/outline.htm\">Course Outline</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/how.htm\">How It Works</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/facilitators.htm\">Course Facilitators</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/privacy.htm\">Your Privacy</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/contact.htm\">Contact Us</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Your Account</b><br />\r\n\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi?action=Register\">Register</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/login.cgi\">Login</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/options.htm\">Manage Account</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/openid.htm\">About OpenID</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Participating</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/cchat.cgi\">Join a Backchannel Chat</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/threads.htm\">Read Discussion Threads</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/newsletter.htm\">Read Daily Newsletter</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/archives.htm\">Newsletter Archives</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?action=viewer\">Browse Blog Posts</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/new_feed.htm\">Add a New Blog Feed</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feeds.htm\">View List of Blogs</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/recordings.htm\">Listen to Recordings</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>Feeds</b><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyposts.xml\">Announcements RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/dailyblogs.xml\">Blog Posts RSS</a><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/opml.xml\">OPML List of Feeds</a><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Contents</b><br />\r\nTBA - will be posted before January 23 - see <a  href=\"http://cck11.mooc.ca\">CCK11 contents</a> for a good indication of what we\'ll do.\r\n</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!-- Body -->\r\n  <div class=\"width75 floatRight\">\r\n     <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n         <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script>\r\n<br>\r\n<h1>Connectivism &amp; Connective Knowledge 2012 Participant Feeds</h1>\r\n<p>The following is a list of the feeds harvested as part of the Connectivism &amp; Connective Knowledge 2012 course. This list may also be obtained as an <a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/opml.xml\">OPML File</a>. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/660\">\'Cher Red</a></b> <br/>By \'cher red.  This is my blog for CCK12.  RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://redguapo.blogspot.com/\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/4347287924697346061/posts/default\">XML</a>]  last Updated: 2012-01-24T06:17:19.647-0<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/684\">Blog de Carmen Gloria Caamao</a></b> <br/>By Carmen Gloria Caamao.   RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://www.cgcaamano.com/\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/4793006409990321836/posts/default\">XML</a>]  last Updated: 2012-01-25T20:05:07.835-0<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/650\">CCK12</a></b> <br/>By Ilona Lantos.  Most recent posts at CCK12 RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://cck12.posterous.com\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://cck12.posterous.com/rss.xml\">XML</a>]  last Updated: <br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/666\">cck12 - Twitter Search</a></b> <br/>By brambruggeman (Bram Bruggeman).   Atom. [<a  href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=cck12\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search.atom?q=cck12\">XML</a>]  last Updated: 2012-01-26T11:16:28Z<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/679\">Change MOOC CCK12</a></b> <br/>By CDATA(19).  This is an ATOM feed. Please feel free to enroll on the forum and get involved in sharing, collaborating and some deep learning! RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://forum.matbury.com\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://forum.matbury.com/feed.php\">XML</a>]  last Updated: 2012-01-26T03:10:39-05:00<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/654\">Chrissi Nerantzi</a></b> <br/>By Chrissi Nerantzi.  bits and pieces RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://chrissinerantzi.wordpress.com\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://chrissinerantzi.wordpress.com/feed/\">XML</a>]  last Updated: Thu, 26 Jan 2012 00:50:54<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/644\">Connecting the dots</a></b> <br/>By brainysmurf.  Learning through risk, networks, trust and serendipity. RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://brainysmurf1234.wordpress.com/feed/\">XML</a>]  last Updated: Wed, 25 Jan 2012 14:49:41<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/672\">Conversando de Conectivismo</a></b> <br/>By Gabriel Bunster.  Mis notas y reflexiones en el contexto del curso de Conectivismo y Conocimiento Conectivo RSS 2.0. [<a  href=\"http://conectivando.blogspot.com/\">HTML</a>][<a  href=\"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8884610487744108684/posts/default\">XML</a>]  last Updated: 2012-01-26T09:07:18.236-0<br/>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<hr/><p><b><a  href=\"http://cck12.mooc.ca/feed/680\">cyberloom</a></b> <br/>By An