seware/d6f5883a9fdd428baa646345966ab0f5/\">Courseware</a></li>\r\n              <li><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/cgi-bin/archive.cgi?page=newsletter.htm\">Archive</a></li>\r\n          </ul>     \r\n		</nav><!-- end main navigation -->\r\n  \r\n    </header><!-- end header -->\r\n\r\n<!-- main content area -->   \r\n<div id=\"main\" class=\"wrapper\">\r\n    \r\n    \r\n<!-- content area -->    \r\n	<section id=\"content\" class=\"wide-content\">\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"grid_3\">\r\n\r\n\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"grid_9\">\r\n\r\n<!-- Generated Content Area --><h1>Opinion</h1>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n  <div class=\"span12\">\r\n     <div class=\"span3\">\r\n\r\nBlogs<br><br>\r\n<p><p><span class=\"post_date\">Feb 11, 2017 1:30 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"https://twitter.com/arasbozkurt/status/710185159191109632/photo/1\"><span class=\"post_title\">Aras Bozkurt On Twitter: \"A Ple Is Not Limited To Web 2.0 Tools, It\'S All About Tools N Learning Community. C The #Nrc01pl Network From Week1 Https://T.Co/Usykjwwea6\"</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\">(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/73\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">NRC01PL on Diigo</a>) \n\n								Tags:				        	        NRC01PL	      			</span></p>\r\n   </div>\r\n   <div class=\"span5\">\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mbrvs4FCmv1r9ed3po1_500.png\">\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n<div class=\"span4\">\r\n<h2>Columnists</h2>\r\n\r\n<h4>The Sixth Estate</h4>\r\n<p><strong><a  href=\"http://sixthestate.net/?p=8002\">Reason No. 217 Why an Ambassador for Religious Freedom is a Silly Idea</a></strong><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/3\"></a>  \r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/journal/\">The Sixth Estate</a> Feb 27, 2013.\r\nI just about fell off my chair when the Globe &#38; Mail&#8217;s Tuesday editorial actually suggested that a suitable first task for newly minted Religious Freedom Ambassador Bennett would be an inspection tour of Tibet: Sending the freshly minted ambassador would surely anger China, a major Canadian trading partner. But if the Harper governments much-touted [...] </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Times&Transcript - Good and Bad</h4>\r\n<p><strong><a  href=\"http://themonctongrimes-dripdrain.blogspot.com/2013/02/feb-26-new-brunswicks-infectious-rot.html\">Feb. 26: New Brunswick\'s infectious rot....</a></strong><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/10\"></a>  \r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/journal/\">The Moncton Times@Transcript - Good and Bad</a> Feb 26, 2013.\r\nVery briefly, today\'s Times and Transcript has very little news, a kiss-up editorial, a hick-town column by Norbert, and and an utterly brainless and irrelevant column by Alan Cochrane. The edition is saved only by superb columns from Alec Bruce and Gwynne Dyer.Oh, as well, there are excellent letters by Denise Melanson of Indian Island and by Barry Ogden of St. John. Ogden\'s letter is particularly an important one in the light of certain propaganda which is the only news in this edition.But ... </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Gwynne Dyer</h4>\r\n<p><strong><a  href=\"http://gwynnedyer.com/2013/victory-in-mali/\">Victory in Mali?</a></strong><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/4\"></a>  \r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/journal/\">Gwynne Dyer</a> Feb 02, 2013.\r\n30 January 2013 Victory in Mali? By Gwynne Dyer As usual, a well-trained Western army has gone through a fierce-looking but virtually untrained force of African rebels like a hot knife through butter. Two weeks ago, the northern half of Mali was entirely under the control of Islamist militants, whose forces were starting to advance [...] </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>David W. Campbell</h4>\r\n<p><strong><a  href=\"http://davidwcampbell.com/?p=5742\">Graham cracker crumbs&#8230;</a></strong><br />\r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/34\"></a>  \r\n<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/journal/\">It&#039;s The Economy, Stupid</a> Feb 26, 2013.\r\nSomeone asked for my thoughts on the departing Shawn Graham. I have mixed views on the Graham government. On the one hand, I thought a number of their initiatives would have been important contributions to renovating New Brunswick. But they had challenges communicating their vision to the public &#8211; starting with the &#8220;Be&#8230; in this [...] </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n   </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br /></div> \r\n<footer   >\r\n  <!-- footer area -->    \r\n\r\n	<div id=\"colophon\" class=\"wrapper clearfix\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<span style=\"float:right\"><img src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/images/Jamlx-DeviantArt-Canada-100.JPG\"></span>\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n<a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca/about.htm\"><img alt=\"gRSShopper\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/img/gRsshopper_88x31.png\"></a>\r\n\r\n<p>Copyright 2015 Stephen Downes ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca\">gRSShopper</a>. <br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n</footer>    \r\n<!-- #end footer area --> \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- jQuery -->\r\n<script src=\"http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1/jquery.min.js\"></script>\r\n<script  >window.jQuery || document.write(\'<script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/libs/jquery-1.9.0.min.js\">\\x3C/script>\')</script>\r\n\r\n<script defer src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/flexslider/jquery.flexslider-min.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n<!-- fire ups - read this file!  -->   \r\n<script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/main.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>',NULL,'HTML','pa