orld</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"economy\">\r\n<h2>Business and Economy</h2>\r\n\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/economy.htm\">Read More: Business and Economy</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"entertainment\">\r\n<h2>Entertainment</h2>\r\n\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/entertainment.htm\">Read More: Entertainment: The Province</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"sports\">\r\n<h2>Sports</h2>\r\n\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/Read More: Sports</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"opinion\">\r\n<h2>Opinion</h2>\r\n<p><p><span class=\"post_date\">Feb 20, 2013 5:26 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.sackvilletribunepost.com/Opinion/2013-02-20/article-3181273/THE-GREEN-BACKPACK-%26ndash%3B-Mass-media-moving-away-from-Climate-change-coverage/1\"><span class=\"post_title\">THE GREEN BACKPACK  Mass media moving away from Climate change coverage</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\"> There is a recognized need for improving coverage of climate change in the mass media. Since 2007 there has been a drop in the mention of climate change and global warming in the Canadian media. In 2007 you had the release of the Fourth Assessment Report of the International Panel on ...</span></p><p><p><span class=\"post_date\">Jan 30, 2013 4:00 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.sackvilletribunepost.com/Opinion/2013-01-30/article-3167163/Province-observing-Black-History-Month/1\"><span class=\"post_title\">Province observing Black History Month</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/261\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">sdoherty@sackvilletribunepost.com</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\"> FREDERICTON, N.B.  The following statement was issued by Randy Dickinson, chair of the New Brunswick Human Rights Commission, about Black History Month:&#13;February was declared Black History Month in Canada in 1995. It is a welcome opportunity to draw attention to an important and little known ...</span></p><p><p><span class=\"post_date\">Jan 25, 2013 3:15 p.m.</span><br/><strong><a  href=\"http://www.sackvilletribunepost.com/Opinion/2013-01-25/article-3163101/National-Non-Smoking-Week-observed/1\"><span class=\"post_title\">National Non-Smoking Week observed</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span class=\"post_author\"><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/author/261\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">sdoherty@sackvilletribunepost.com</a></span>\r\n<br/><span class=\"post_body\"> FREDERICTON, N.B.  The following message was issued by Healthy and Inclusive Communities Minister Dorothy Shephard on the occasion of National Non-Smoking Week, Jan. 20-26:&#13;I am pleased to recognize National Non-Smoking Week. This year\'s theme is Live, work, play...even better smoke-free.&#13;It ...</span></p>\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/opinion.htm\">Read More: Opinion</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"videos\">\r\n<h2>Videos</h2>\r\n\r\n<br><a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/opinion.htm\">Read More: Videos</a><br>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section id=\"fifthcolumn\">\r\n<h2>Fifth Column</h2>\r\n</section>\r\n</div>',NULL,'email',' ',' ','yes','yes','no','1',1358202059,1486878601,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'dailynewsletter.htm','1486878601','yes','Daily','00',NULL,'00','no',NULL),(197,'About Moncton Free Press',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1 property=\"dc:title\">About Us</h1>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><span>Mission</span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>We want to create a bilingual publication for the Greater Moncton area population. <strong></strong></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>We want to present the voices which are too often absent or ignored in the traditional media. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>We want to provide independent, reliable, precise, diverse and relevant information for our readers which will feed their reflection and enable them to make informed choices about important society issues. We want to offer a balance in the expressed views, make a plurality of voices heard: women, men, anglophones, francophones, aboriginals, immigrants, etc. We want to give people a tool which will enable them to express themselves freely, without censorship, and to play a more active role in their local democracy. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>This publication will cover local, provincial, national and international news. It will include editorials, columns, opinion letters and reports. Topics will include politics, economy, energy, environment, democracy, social issues, amongst others. This publication will also encourage other forms of expression such as caricatures, poems, etc. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><span>Principles</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Openness</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Inclusion</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-democracy</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Honesty</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Integrity</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Professionalism/responsibility</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Freedom of expression</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Independence</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Diversity of views </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><span>Mission</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Nous voulons offrir  la population du Grand Moncton une publication bilingue.<strong></strong></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Nous voulons faire entendre les points de vue qui sont trop souvent absents ou ignors dans les mdias traditionnels. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Nous voulons fournir aux lecteurs des informations </span><span lang=\"fr\">indpendantes, fiables, prcises, diverses et pertinentes </span><span>qui vont alimenter leur rflexion et leur permettre de faire des choix clairs au sujet denjeux importants de socit. Nous voulons offrir un quilibre au niveau des opinions exprimes, faire entendre une pluralit de voix: des femmes, des hommes, des anglophones, des francophones, des autochtones, des immigrants, etc. Nous voulons offrir aux citoyens un outil qui va leur permettre de sexprimer librement, sans censure et de jouer un rle plus actif dans leur dmocratie locale. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Cette publication abordera les nouvelles locales, nationales et internationales. Elle inclura des ditoriaux, des chroniques, des lettres dopinion et des reportages. Les sujets couverts porteront, entre autres, sur la politique, lconomie, lnergie, lenvironnement, la dmocratie et les enjeux sociaux. Cette publication encouragera aussi les autres formes dexpression ou dart telles que les caricatures, les pomes, etc. etc. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><span>Principes</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Ouverture desprit</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Inclusion</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-dmocratie</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Honntet</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Intgrit</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Professionnalisme / responsabilit</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Libert dexpression </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Indpendance </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>-Diversit dopinions </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-size: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">Publication policy</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>The editorial committee has the right to refuse any submitted text for the following reasons: :</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>1- </span><span>It contains spelling, grammatical or syntax errors. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>2- </span><span>Its too long or too short</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>3- </span><span>It contains statements which may be considered as libel or hate speech </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>4- </span><span>It contains information which is not verifiable </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>5- </span><span>It contains plagiarized text.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>If a text is refused, the editorial committee will return it to its author and ask him/her to make the necessary changes before publishing it. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>The use of pseudonyms is allowed, but authors need to identify themselves (full contact information : name, phone number, postal address and email address) to the editorial committee.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><span>Politique de publication du journal</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Le comit de rdaction se rserve le droit de refuser tout texte pourles raisons suivantes :</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>1- </span><span>Sil contient des fautes dorthographe, de grammaire ou de syntaxe</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>2- </span><span>Sil est trop long ou trop court</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>3- </span><span>Sil contient des propos jugs diffamatoires ou haineux</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>4- </span><span>Sil contient des informations qui ne sont pas vrifiables</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>5- </span><span>Sil contient des informations plagies</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Si un texte est refus, le comit ditorial le rendra  son auteur en lui demandant de faire les corrections ncessaires pour quil soit publi. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>Lutilisation de pseudonymes est permise. Toutefois, les auteurs devront sidentifier auprs du comit de rdaction en fournissant leurs coordonnes compltes (nom, numro de tlphone, adresse postale, courriel).</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-size: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">Varia (type of organization) </span></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>In the long term, the group wants to adopt a cooperative structure for the MFP. However, after examining the legal and administrative requirements to become a cooperative, the group has decided its too early for that step. All agree on the value of a cooperative system, but we will wait until the publication has a solid team to pursue that option. </span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span>All agree on the fact that all volunteers / members of the MFP should sign an ownership statement (to state that the MFP belongs to its members and no one can claim its property if they decide to leave it.) Flix will look up different models of ownerships statements and suggest some to us at the next meeting.</span>','Friday','<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\"><head>\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"content-type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\r\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\r\n    <!-- title -->\r\n  <title>About Moncton Free Press ~ Moncton Free Press</title>\r\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"\">\r\n    <meta name=\"author\" content=\"\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- scripts -->\r\n\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n    <!-- Le javascript\r\n    ================================================== -->\r\n    <!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster -->\r\n    <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/jquery.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/google-code-prettify/prettify.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-transition.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-alert.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-modal.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-dropdown.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-scrollspy.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-tab.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-tooltip.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"http://course.downes.ca/assets/js/bootstrap-popover.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"ht